    "longBusinessSummary": "Bamboo Capital Joint Stock Company, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the renewable energy, real estate, and financial services businesses in Vietnam. The company is involved in the management and investment consultancy activities; construction installation; and wholesale of other machinery and equipment, and food, including milk, dairy products, and confectionery, as well as products processed from cereals, flour, starch, coffee, and cocoa. It also engages in real estate activities; trading of own or rented property and land use rights; wholesale of agricultural raw materials and live animals; sale of motorcycle parts and accessories; renting and leasing of automobiles; and maintenance and repair of motor vehicles. In addition, the company is involved in the construction of roads and railways, buildings, utility projects, and other civil engineering projects; site preparation; building completion and finishing; other specialized construction activities; mining of other non-ferrous metal ores, iron ores, thorium ores, and uranium; quarrying of stone, sand, gravel, and clay; and electric power generation, transmission, and distribution through solar and wind power. Further, it engages in the wholesale of construction materials and other installation equipment; sawmilling, planning, and preserving of wood; manufacturing of veneer, plywood, and veneer panels, as well as builders' carpentry and joinery; and provision of non-life insurance products and investment activities. The company was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.",
